I love this app. It takes a little bit of time to get set up, but it's well worth it if you want to do any sort of analysis . Reading other reviews on here, it's clear that people are simply not taking this time, and have not tried other massively more expensive telemetry solutions. I can hook up an external 10Hz GPS, an OBD-II Bluetooth dongle, and a GoPro for dual video recording, and it just works! Find me something else that comes close for this price (accessories included) and I'll eat my hat.   I show up at the track, mount my phone, turn on my GPS, plug in my OBD-II dongle, and fire up the GoPro, and then just load a track and go! End of session or day, I review. I learn. I go faster! It's amazing, and frequently reminds me that slow is fast as I think I've done a killer lap and then learn I'm actually 1-2s off my pace.  Great job Harald, thanks for the very dedicated support, and keep up the good work.

replyContent: In case laps are not recognized, there is either a problem with GPS accuracy or the track set loaded. For the former, please make sure you mount the device as recommended in illustration #3 in Quick Reference. Multi lap recordings can be split after the fact, please drop us a not to Harry@gps-laptimer.de for instructions.

replyContent: Please contact us at Harry@gps-laptimer.de. A low OBD update rate is due to some compatibility issues between car / adapter / app an can probably be fixed.

Do not buy this app.. Complete waste of money. Had a free app before and worked really well for free. Tried this all day at my last track day with full 3g service and did not work once... Maybe it needs to be hard wired on to the car but you are not allowed in the uk and why would a free app work over this when I paid ¬£20... Absolutely rubbish and biggest waste of my money..
replyContent: A 3G network has no influence on LapTimer operation. The part that is important is GPS. You need to take care you have optimal GPS accuracy and your track day's configuration loaded (Load Track). Please check the health status available in the status bar. LapTimer checks e.g. accuracy and general configuration and will offer solutions.
